I chose this hotel because of the good reviews online, but my experience was disappointing from the start. We couldn’t even find the place easily. We had confirmed our arrival for 2–3 PM but ended up arriving around 6 PM. We called ahead at 5:30, and they said the room was ready. When we got there, someone was still cleaning the bathroom, and the strong smell of bleach made the room uncomfortable.

I booked the Royal Suite. The AC didn’t work properly, and even after reporting it, no one showed up to fix it. The shower pressure was weak, and the “free breakfast” was barely worth mentioning.

We paid the remaining balance in cash at night since we had to leave early. When we asked for a receipt, the front desk staff said they’d give it to us before checkout — we never got it.

What bothered me the most was the staff pressuring us to write a review on the spot. My brother was asked to scan a QR code, write the review while the staff watched, and then the staff even took a photo of it. I was asked too, but I refused and said I’d do it later.

Overall, I would not recommend this place. There are better hotels nearby — skip this one.

The rooms at the hotel were dirty and used. It costed almost 4000/-for the night for such an unhygienic room. Housekeeping did not clean the bathroom which still smelled strongly of urine and used soaps/hygiene products were still in the washroom. Bedsheets were covered in assorted stains and did not look like they had even been changed since the last customer. We had to change 2 rooms to be comfortable enough to stay the night. We were told breakfast will be 7am to 10:30AM but when we asked staff if we could come and eat by 9:45AM, we were told that breakfast is finished so you will have to manage. Outside food like Swiggy/zomato are NOT ALLOWED to be ordered at the hotel and so if you do not eat by the prescribed times, you can starve or walk to the nearest restaurant in the middle of the night endangering yourself. Airport transfer cab was included in our stay but refused to stop anywhere along the way to allow guests to purchase supplies and/or eat something before being dropped.

Location of this hotel is 5 minutes from the airport and is the ONLY thing about this hotel that makes sense. They have decent reviews online but hotel photos listed on the booking websites are very old and do not represent its current state.

Would not recommend booking this hotel due to budget, poor service and most importantly, poor hygiene.

We stayed at Pristine Residency, Ahmedabad, as a family of four for a one-night transit stay before our 5 PM flight the next day, and it was a comfortable and convenient experience overall. The hotel’s proximity to the airport—just about 5 minutes by car—made it an ideal choice. Their complimentary airport drop-off service was a big plus and saved us the hassle of arranging transport.

We had booked one Executive and one Deluxe room. Both rooms were clean and well-maintained, with basic amenities in place. The Executive room was a bit more spacious and had a better layout, while the Deluxe room was compact but still comfortable. Beds were cozy, the bathrooms were clean, and the ACs worked well in both rooms.

The staff was courteous and responsive throughout our stay, which made the experience smoother, especially when traveling with family. The complimentary breakfast in the morning was average—limited spread and not particularly flavorful—but it served its purpose. On the other hand, lunch and dinner at their in-house restaurant were genuinely enjoyable, with fresh and tasty dishes that satisfied both adults and kids.

The hotel ambience is simple and functional—don’t expect luxury—but for a short stay, it’s perfectly adequate. They also allowed us to store luggage after check-out, since our flight was later in the day, which was really helpful.

Overall, Pristine Residency is a practical, budget-friendly option for families looking for a short and comfortable stay close to Ahmedabad airport.

Hotel Review: ★☆☆☆☆ (Should be zero stars)

This was, hands down, the worst hotel experience of my life — and I’m not exaggerating. If I could give this place negative stars, I would. Calling it a "hotel" is an insult to the word itself.

From the moment I stepped in, I regretted booking it. The lobby smelled like a mix of mold and cheap disinfectant. The staff looked bored, irritated, and completely uninterested in helping anyone. I was made to wait 30 minutes just to check in, even though no one else was at the counter.

The room? An absolute nightmare. The bed was sunken in the middle and covered with suspicious stains. The sheets were clearly unwashed — I found hair and even what looked like crumbs between them. The bathroom was a horror show: cracked tiles, black mold creeping along the shower walls, and the toilet didn’t even flush properly. There were bugs. Yes, actual bugs crawling on the floor and walls. I felt disgusted just touching anything.

There was no Wi-Fi, no hot water, no soundproofing. I could hear the couple next door arguing all night, dogs barking outside, and what sounded like construction at 2 a.m. It was like trying to sleep in the middle of a war zone.

Honestly, this place should be shut down by the health department. It’s dirty, unhygienic, loud, depressing, and run by people who clearly don’t care. It felt like a punishment just staying there.

Do yourself a favor — sleep in your car, a park bench, anywhere but this disaster of a hotel.

text.text:
We stayed at Pristine Residency, Ahmedabad, as a family of four for a one-night transit stay before our 5 PM flight the next day, and it was a comfortable and convenient experience overall. The hotel’s proximity to the airport—just about 5 minutes by car—made it an ideal choice. Their complimentary airport drop-off service was a big plus and saved us the hassle of arranging transport.

We had booked one Executive and one Deluxe room. Both rooms were clean and well-maintained, with basic amenities in place. The Executive room was a bit more spacious and had a better layout, while the Deluxe room was compact but still comfortable. Beds were cozy, the bathrooms were clean, and the ACs worked well in both rooms.

The staff was courteous and responsive throughout our stay, which made the experience smoother, especially when traveling with family. The complimentary breakfast in the morning was average—limited spread and not particularly flavorful—but it served its purpose. On the other hand, lunch and dinner at their in-house restaurant were genuinely enjoyable, with fresh and tasty dishes that satisfied both adults and kids.

The hotel ambience is simple and functional—don’t expect luxury—but for a short stay, it’s perfectly adequate. They also allowed us to store luggage after check-out, since our flight was later in the day, which was really helpful.

Overall, Pristine Residency is a practical, budget-friendly option for families looking for a short and comfortable stay close to Ahmedabad airport.
